This map was made with the intention of balancing out snipers, so players can dominate the map with SMGs and Shotguns instead of just Rifles. The fort inside was designed like a lazer tag map, so there are plenty of corners and passageways for tactical presiscion. There also is a long hallway on the side for those who are fans of snipers. 

Note:
In the sniper hall, the corner has a crack which leads all the way to the other side, so one can snipe through the crack. It's awesome for a loltastic experience!

This is a Battlefield 3 map remake "Seine Crossing" was the name. I just picked this part of the map and decided to stretch the Source Engine's legs a bit to see what it could do, this is what came of it. Some parts were re-imagined for playability purposes or ease of creation (learned my lesson about doing diagonal things real fast)
Anyway it turns out it's not a very good map for de_ or cs_ (bombsite or hostage rescue) because of how open it is, kind of limits the strategical part of it. So I just made it into a deathmatch. I provided a .txt with 44 spawn locations that should be in the correct format for CSSDM. If you do not want to run CSSDM and just want to run round-based matches, there are 20 spawn points for either team and a buyzone encompassing all of them. I did not include a .nav file, on final release there will be one.
MAKE SURE THAT YOUR WATER REFLECTIONS ARE TURNED TO SIMPLE REFLECTIONS OR REFLECT WORLD IF YOU WANT TO PLAY ON THIS MAP. FAILING TO DO SO WILL RESULT IN UNPLAYABLE FPS.
Also HDR is known to be buggy so I would recommend turning that off as well.

Dev Notes:
As stated earlier, I modeled this after the Battlefield 3 map "Seine Crossing" which turned out to be a, fairly large task. I took about 95 hours over the course of 10 days to get what you see here (including the optimizations). I did ignore my girlfriend for these 10 days and I did not pay attention in most classes. So I'm taking a (I think) well deserved break from it and going to spend some time paying attention in class and hanging out with my girlfriend.

Known bugs:
 - The trim on the outermost part of the bridges (on top of the stone) is missing
 - HDR is more problematic than it is pretty (won't be included in the final game)
 - If you have the water reflections turned to anything but "Simple Reflections" or "Reflect World" you will likely get less than 40 fps when facing the water (this is mainly due to the size of the map and how much the water reflects back. I've done many optimizations, tried different water, changed the water LOD to always render cheap water, it all basically gives you the same outcome)
 - There's a couple lighting bugs here and there but if you see any let me know.
 - A map overview is in the works

The future plans, however are:

- Create 3d skybox to match up with the level so it doesn't look so bland and just like the level ends (since it kind of does)
- Create minimap overlay
- Fix any bugs that are reported or I find between now and then
Still working on this project but great fun. Enjoy.

This is just the first beta of a map that I made for my friend's CS:S server. 
You'll definately want about...20 people playing for it to be really crazy. 
We have been playing it with GunGame:Deathmatch. I would also recommend that you turn the servers gravity to about 500 to prevent death from falling too much. Oh, and as Screenshot E shows, that big black mass in the middle actually has water like properties. I was having alot of problems with getting the water to render right, it kept letting you see through walls and what not, so I placed that illusionary cover over it. 

Hope ya enjoy ^.^

Please PM me any real problems you face, or if you have a suggestion to add into it. 

The final version will not be released here, but on my website for the server.

This map is much larger and is actually the largest of the 4 maps. both teams start on opposite sides of the map. From spawn you can go several different directions. You can go down the road and use the broken tanks as cover as you run to the other spawn, or you can try to run for one of the 4 guard towers on the 4 corners of the map. There is also a house in this map which has a basement. In the basesment is a few boxes that you can hide behind. The house itself is nothing really great, it's got windows and a few things inside, but nothing to get really excited about. In the middle of the map is a guard house which has 2 main guard rooms. The guard house itself is an excellent piece of structure to hide behind. If you can think of a way to use it to your advantage to navigate yourself to the other team's spawn, you might get some easy kills. This map is overall a good map for dm. The size of it is perfect and the types of structure in the map work good for a dm server.

I based this map off of the Ghiaccio level from JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken: Ougon no Kaze for the PS2. I had to take some liberties because the game is designed around 1v1 battles, so I had to add more objects in order to make the map more suitable for a deathmatch gamemode.

This is my first real time making a map, I am open to any and all criticism and suggestions.

So.... its time for a beta release. Why a beta? I currently can't test this on a server.

A short story for the map and CS:Real Tournament.....
Barsylt is a wooden mansion based in sweden and builded for the scientest "Feodore Barsylt". He invented new revolutionary pick up systems like the "Hot-loader" and the "Health-Crypt". Barsylt works for the "UnHarmed" Corporation, an underground organization that earn their money with a brutal bet -"Real Tournament". They are kidnapping terrorists and kill them in this "game". The opponents are highly payed corrupt police forces from the whole world, but they pay most of the time with their life........

If you find something like glitches or bugs, please tell me. Thanks......

Spawns:
- placed: 40 - max players: 26

Spawner:
-12 Hot-loader Weaponspawner
-14 Health-Crypt hp booster + The big hp booster (300hp)
-6 Grenade disp. 3in1 = 18 spawner
-2 Scout/AWP disp.

=47 spawner

Weapons:
All - The autosnipers and the tmp are missing.

Startweapons:
-Random Pistol and a mac10 -The pistol changes all 10 sec. to an other pistol. That means if all start at the same time, all players have the same weapons.

True Player:
It plays endless, it plays fully random, it plays at your choice and you can stop it by pressing the track that currently runs. All these tracks are prod. by The Real Unique Entertainment and 3 of them are made exclusive for this player. I've included also a progressbar for every song and I've installed a spammlock. If you press the buttons more than 7 times, all buttons wll be locked. If the track that currently runs ends, the buttons will be unlocked again.

Performance
I7-4930K at 4.5GHz, SLI 980ti 8K: 130fps, 4K: nearly always 300 fps
Single GPU 980ti 8K: 65 fps, 4K: 200 fps, WQHD: nearly always 300 frames
